## `compare_inputs.m` — sketch

Signature: `compare_inputs(ulg_path, out_dir)` — mirrors `run_sysid.m` shape.

Config: `cfg.regime = 'mc'` (default), `cfg.fmin_Hz = 0.05`, `cfg.fmax_Hz = 10`, `cfg.coh_cutoff = 0.6`, `cfg.np = 2`, `cfg.nz = 0`, `cfg.min_segment_s = 10`. Same defaults as `run_sysid.m` so the comparison is apples-to-apples.

Main flow:

```matlab
function compare_inputs(ulg_path, out_dir)
% Sanity check: does using vehicle_rates_setpoint as the sysID input yield
% the same identified TF as using vehicle_torque_setpoint?
% Expected: NO — torque is the plant input (identifies P_rate),
% rates_setpoint is the plant input *to the closed rate loop* (identifies T_rate).

% addpath + cfg + out_dir setup mirror run_sysid.m lines 24-37

[D, ~, ~] = ulg_to_csv(ulg_path, out_dir);
D = derive_signals(D);

required = {'vehicle_angular_velocity_0','vehicle_rates_setpoint_0','vehicle_torque_setpoint_0'};
for k = 1:numel(required)
    if ~isfield(D, required{k}) || ~isfield(D.(required{k}), 'rpy')
        error('missing topic or .rpy: %s', required{k});
    end
end

base_t  = D.vehicle_angular_velocity_0.t;
vs_base = D.vehicle_angular_velocity_0.vtol_state;

% Pick mc segment (or fw with --regime fw via cfg toggle — defaulted to mc).
sl = segment_by_vtol_state(base_t, vs_base, 3, cfg.min_segment_s);
if isempty(sl); error('no MC segment >= %.1fs', cfg.min_segment_s); end
[~, j] = max(sl(:,2)-sl(:,1));
t_seg = base_t(sl(j,1):sl(j,2));
dt    = median(diff(t_seg));
fmax  = min(cfg.fmax_Hz, 0.4/dt);
t_zero = (t_seg - t_seg(1));

fig_dir = fullfile(out_dir, 'figures', 'mc');
if ~isfolder(fig_dir); mkdir(fig_dir); end

verdicts = {};
for ax = 1:3
    ax_name = cfg.axes{ax};

    % Common output signal
    y = interp_safe(D.vehicle_angular_velocity_0.t, ...
                    D.vehicle_angular_velocity_0.rpy(:,ax), t_seg);
    y = nonlinear_detrend(y, t_zero);

    % Input A: torque_setpoint (current run_sysid choice)
    u_A = interp_safe(D.vehicle_torque_setpoint_0.t, ...
                      D.vehicle_torque_setpoint_0.rpy(:,ax), t_seg);
    u_A = nonlinear_detrend(u_A, t_zero);
    P_A = identify_plant(u_A, y, t_zero, cfg.fmin_Hz, fmax, cfg.np, cfg.nz, cfg.coh_cutoff);

    % Input B: rates_setpoint (the alternative being verified)
    u_B = interp_safe(D.vehicle_rates_setpoint_0.t, ...
                      D.vehicle_rates_setpoint_0.rpy(:,ax), t_seg);
    u_B = nonlinear_detrend(u_B, t_zero);
    P_B = identify_plant(u_B, y, t_zero, cfg.fmin_Hz, fmax, cfg.np, cfg.nz, cfg.coh_cutoff);

    plot_overlay(P_A, P_B, fig_dir, ax_name);
    verdicts{end+1} = compute_verdict(P_A, P_B, ax_name, cfg);
end

write_verdict_report(fullfile(out_dir, 'compare_inputs.txt'), verdicts, ulg_path, cfg);
fprintf('[compare_inputs] done. outdir=%s\n', out_dir);
end
```

Helpers in the same file:

- **`plot_overlay(P_A, P_B, fig_dir, axis_name)`** — single figure per axis, 3 subplots (mag dB, phase deg, coherence). Each subplot shows two curves (A: torque→rates, B: rates_sp→rates) plus measured-FRF dots in two colors. If `P_A.tf` and/or `P_B.tf` fit successfully, also overlay each TF's `freqresp` line. Save as `compare_<axis>_bode.png` + `.fig`. Style mirrors `make_plots.m::Bode` (lines 14-49).

- **`compute_verdict(P_A, P_B, axis_name, cfg)`** — measures the gap on the joint-coherent band (where both `P_A.coh` and `P_B.coh` exceed `cfg.coh_cutoff` after interpolating both onto a common log-spaced frequency grid in `[fmin, fmax]`). Returns a struct:
  ```
  v.axis            = 'roll'
  v.f_band          = [f_lo, f_hi]
  v.mag_rms_dB      = RMS of (mag_A - mag_B) in dB on the joint band
  v.mag_max_dB      = max |mag_A - mag_B| in dB
  v.phase_rms_deg   = RMS of unwrapped phase diff on the joint band
  v.coh_min         = min(P_A.coh, P_B.coh) on the joint band
  v.A_DC_dB         = mag of P_A at the lowest joint-coherent frequency
  v.B_DC_dB         = same for P_B (expected ~0 dB if B is closed-loop, very large if it's the plant)
  v.verdict         = 'SAME' if mag_rms_dB<3 and phase_rms_deg<10, else 'DIFFER'
  v.reason          = if DIFFER, a sentence: 'P_A identifies open-loop plant (DC gain X dB); P_B identifies closed-loop rate response (DC gain Y dB).'
  ```

- **`write_verdict_report(path, verdicts, ulg_path, cfg)`** — emits `compare_inputs.txt`:
  ```
  ULG: /path/to/log.ulg
  Run: 2026-05-18 17:34:21
  Topology check: u_A = vehicle_torque_setpoint_0.rpy, u_B = vehicle_rates_setpoint_0.rpy, y = vehicle_angular_velocity_0.rpy
  Frequency band evaluated: 0.050–10.000 Hz   Coherence cutoff: 0.60

  Axis    Band [Hz]       |Δmag| RMS    |Δmag| max    |Δphase| RMS    A(DC)   B(DC)   Verdict
  roll    0.10–9.50       8.4 dB        12.3 dB       42.1 deg         -6 dB   +1 dB   DIFFER
  pitch   ...
  yaw     ...

  Interpretation:
    Input A (torque_setpoint -> rates) identifies the open-loop plant P_rate(s).
    Input B (rates_setpoint  -> rates) identifies the closed-loop rate transfer T_rate(s)
      = C_rate*P_rate / (1 + C_rate*P_rate).
    These are different objects in the rate-control loop topology, so they should not
    match in general. The verdict above quantifies the gap for this dataset.
  ```

- **`interp_safe`** and **`nonlinear_detrend`** — already exist in `run_sysid.m` (line 275) and `sysID_tool` respectively. I duplicate the 4-line `interp_safe` locally (same pattern as `run_sysid.m::identify_axis`) and call `nonlinear_detrend` from the path added at the top.

